            <h3>YELP CAMP</h3>
            <p>
                Built as the final project for Colt Steele's "The Web Developer
                Bootcamp", this is a fully responsive back-end focussed CRUD
                application using MongoDb, Express and Node.
                <br />
                <br />
                The application allows users to submit, rate and review
                campsites showing an index of all campsites within a fully
                interactive cluster map using the mapbox API.
                <br />
                <br />
                This app features:
                <br />
                - User authentication and authorisation using passport local and
                MongoDb.
                <br />
                - Multiple API calls to Mapbox and Cloudinary.
                <br />
                - Form validation through Javascipt and server side
                authentication using joi.
                <br />
                - Basic password security using bcrypt.
                <br />
                <br />
                While this project was a code-along, I made every effort to
                write the code before going through each section in order to
                understand every line written and key concepts.
            </p>
